293
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,800
[GREY] So how did it go?

294
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,100
[PINA] They're taking a few
captives...

295
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:17,833
We're picking up the expenses,

296
00:17:17,933 --> 00:17:20,233
and providing security for their
envoys...

297
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:22,700
And we're giving them tax‐exempt
trade in the city.

298
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:26,366
[GREY] I'd be waiting for their
true intentions to be revealed.

299
00:17:26,466 --> 00:17:31,300
I'm assuming they'll be leaving
some soldiers here for a while?

300
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:33,133
[PINA] Mm‐mm... They said they'd
be pulling their forces out.

301
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:34,633
[GREY] That's ridiculous, Your
Majesty!

302
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:36,266
You don't win a battle like this

303
00:17:36,366 --> 00:17:37,833
and not have any demands.

304
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:39,366
This whole thing feels odd.

305
00:17:39,466 --> 00:17:41,233
[PINA] Right? Goes against
everything

306
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,366
you taught me about negotiating
victory...

307
00:17:43,466 --> 00:17:45,833
It just doesn't make any sense.

308
00:17:45,933 --> 00:17:48,566
[PINA] I'd like to know the kind
of magic Hamilton used.

309
00:17:48,666 --> 00:17:50,633
(consternation)

310
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:52,566
[YOJI] Yep. Her... and her.

311
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:55,100
[YOJI] And I think she might be
able to help too.

312
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,366
[SHINO] The girl with the
feathers on her head?

313
00:17:57,466 --> 00:17:59,533
[YOJI] Yeah.

314
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,200
[MARI] What a surprise,
they're all girls.

315
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,100
[YOJI] That's just a
coincidence.

316
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,466
[SHINO] Uh huh... I'm so not
buying this.

317
00:18:04,566 --> 00:18:06,266
[YOJI] Well it's still just a
coincidence.

318
00:18:06,366 --> 00:18:07,800
[MARI] Of course... Sure.

319
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:10,566
[YOJI] Great! Glad we all agree!

320
00:18:10,666 --> 00:18:13,233
[MARI] Well... obviously we
can't simply

321
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:16,300
leave these women behind enemy
lines.

322
00:18:17,066 --> 00:18:18,266
(rotor noises)

323
00:18:18,366 --> 00:18:21,000
[CIVILIANS] Thank you!
Thanks for everything!

324
00:18:32,666 --> 00:18:35,400
[TOMITA] So... should we be
heading out too, sir?

325
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,400
[KURATA] Uuh. Don't we still
need the girls?

326
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:38,933
[YOJI] They're in negotiations,

327
00:18:39,033 --> 00:18:40,433
why they came here in the first
place.

328
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:42,500
[TOMITA] Oh right I almost
forgot about that.

329
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:46,166
[YOJI] Yeah... we did come here
for a reason.

330
00:18:46,266 --> 00:18:47,600
And instead, we wound up dealing
with

331
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,733
a buncha jerks trying to tear
the place apart.

332
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:56,513
[LELEI] We were hoping to sell
these.

333
00:18:56,613 --> 00:18:59,580
[RYUDO] Well... a splendid
dragon scale you've got there.

334
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:02,413
[RYUDO] At first glance...
looks like it's from a wyvern.

335
00:19:02,513 --> 00:19:05,613
[LELEI] That's right.
[RYUDO] So how many do you have?

336
00:19:05,713 --> 00:19:07,880
[LELEI] 200.
[RYUDO] 200?!

337
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:09,680
[LELEI] Also, the Empire has
given us

338
00:19:09,780 --> 00:19:11,980
